Not looking for any trades. Gun was only shot once by my wife and is in new condition with original box and 1 magazine. I live on Fort Hood but can meet near the killeen area. Price is $315. Must be willing to sign bill of sale and provide TX ID or CHL.

The CW380 pistol has a 2.58 inch barrel, an overall length of 4.96 inches and a height of just 3.9 inches. It weighs just 10.2 ounces without a magazine. The pistol has a black polymer frame and features 4140 steel inserts molded into the front and back of the frame for added rigidity. It has a machined, solid 416 matte stainless steel slide and a textured polymer grip.

The Kahr CW380 features a lock breech, modified Browning type recoil lug, and utilizes Kahr's seven patents including the "safe cam" action found in all Kahr pistols. The result is a micro-compact pistol with very little recoil and quick follow-up shots. The pistol features drift adjustable white bar-dot combat rear sight and pinned-in polymer front sight.

Differences between the Kahr CW380 and Kahr P380 models include: the CW series has a conventional rifled barrel instead of the match grade polygonal barrel found on P models; the CW slide stop lever is MIM (metal-injection-molded) instead of machined; the CW series slide has fewer machining operations, and uses simple roll marking instead of engraved markings; the P380 comes with two magazines, but the CW series comes with one 6 rd steel magazine with flush baseplate. Lastly, the slide locks back after firing the last round – another feature missing on a number of other value-priced compact semi-auto pistols. The durability and reliability of the CW380 model makes it a strong consideration as a backup gun for law enforcement.

USP Compacts are smaller and lighter than large frame USPs. The reduction in trigger reach and grip circumference increases concealability and enhances shooting ergonomics. title: For Sale:  Browning A5 Light 20ga. Invector Chokes, 1st yr. Miroku prod.
postcontent:
This is a beautiful shotgun just in time for Dove season and ready for the Ringnecks. Of course it is so nice, that a collector might not want to use it as Browning quit making this model in 1997 I believe. The date code on this is PR prefix which means it was made in 1987 which was the first year that the Light Twenty were the Auto-5 Light 20 Miroku. The Invector Chokes didn't become standard until 1993, so this was pretty much a first production, loaded shotgun after a layoff from production.

Browning A-5 Light Twenty with the Invector Choke system and vented rib barrel. Comes with three chokes and the tool. You can also easily adjust this shotgun for light or heavy loads depending where you put the "Friction Ring". Very simple and the instruction manual has pictures.

I've looked this shotgun over trying to find flaws and it is near impossible. The blueing is flawless, cant find a chip or speck or scratch. The stocks are near perfect, showing a couple very light handling marks. They won't show up in pictures.

The bolt and loading port don't even have use marks. This was someone's baby and didn't get used much if at all. It even had the sticker on the end that I removed and put on the invector choke manual because I didn't like the look of a sticker on such bright and shiny blueing. Gun looks way better in person.

title: For Sale:   North American Arms .22 Short Pistol, 1 & 12" Barrel 5 Round Revolver with 25 Rounds of Ammo & Rosewood Grips.
postcontent:
The North American Arms .22 Short *(it has a limited production that runs early each year)*, it is the World's smallest, lightest and most popular five-shot Mini-Revolver they make if you can find one in stock online. Gunbroker has some up for auction.

Like all North American Arms Mini-Revolvers they are covered by a lifetime warranty against defects in material, workmanship and repairs as long as you pay for the parts used or labor. 

I sent it in for a new cylinder bolt and it came back with the new cylinder bolt and a upgraded notched cylinder without any charges to me for the parts or labor.

I have had this pistol for for over 10 years and have only used it at the range and in my back yard shooting skunks and troublesome squirrels. It is still in like new condition. Comes with 25 rounds of ammo to get you started, more ammo available on Gunbroker at a fair price with fair shipping fees.

This little pistol could save your life, it will not show in your pocket and it is vary easy to find. 
The most vulnerable place can be in backing one out on the toilet, here is one place this little pistol will save your live as well as other places especially at night when you are alone.

To buy this pistol with ammo please send an email and I will meet you in a busy shopping area. 

If you buy this pistol online you will still have to pay the shipping fee before it is shipped and a transfer fee ounce it arrives, if you buy my pistol all you will only pay a total of $17.00 for all fees, $10 transfer and a $7 background fee = $17.

As with every North American Arms Mini-Revolver, the hammer need not rest on an empty chamber. Using the original half-way notch cylinder in between chambers, (See picture number two for the notches, you will also notice the firing pin which rests in the notch) the hammers firing pin may rest safely and securely without chance of accidental discharge.

It also has a second safety with the hammer puled back to the first click, (see picture number one) this keeps the hammer away from the cartridge. 
Both are good safety's but the rest in the notch is the best to use, this safety will insure any chance of an accidental discharge even if it is dropped on a rock or a hard surface.

Thank you for viewing my listing.
